The paper deals with the problem of embedding graphs in the plane, which is a classic topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The concept of spanners is a fundamental one in graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS), and the paper focuses on the geometric properties of spanners. The paper also discusses the complexity of various problems related to spanners, such as deciding whether a graph admits a straight-line drawing with a given spanning ratio, which falls under computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also touches on the topic of graph theory (cs.DM) and the analysis of algorithms (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implications of the results, such as the trade-off between spanning ratio and edge-length ratio, which could be relevant to applications in computer networks and communication systems (cs.SI).
